        <div class="wrap">
            <div class="container main">

                <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-general.ejs %>

                <article class="blade wrapper content">
                    <!-- article -->

                    <div>
                      <h1>Port Forwarding :: D-Link</h1>
                      <p> <i>This is the 2nd step of the Port Forwarding, click <a href="/Fernzugriff/Der_DDNS_Dienst/">here</a> to get to the beginning of the manual.</i></p>
                      <br>
                        <h3>Step 1</h3>
                        <p>To access the user interface of your router open the following address with your internet browser <a href="http://192.168.0.1">192.168.0.1</a>. The default login is username = admin and password is left blank. Navigate to the <em>Portweiterleitung</em> in the <em>Erweitert</em> menu (s. below).</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <amp-img
                          on="tap:Dlink_01en"
                          role="button"
                          tabindex="0"
                          src="/images/Internet_Access/Dlink_01en.jpg" width="480" height="311" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                      </amp-img>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <p>Go to Advanced/Portforwarding to set a new port forwarding rule for your camera.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Step 2</h3>
                        <p>Check the box in front of the service and give your camera a name in the <em>Name</em> field. Type your camera´s IP address into the field <em>IP Address</em> underneath. Set both the <em>Öffentlicher Port</em> and <em>Privater Port</em> to the port of your camera. For your first camera this is "8081", for your second camera it´s 8082 etc. Then choose TCP as <em>Datenverkehrstyp</em> and click on <em>Einstellungen speichern</em> to save the service.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <amp-img
                          on="tap:Dlink_02en"
                          role="button"
                          tabindex="0"
                          src="/images/Internet_Access/Dlink_02en.jpg" width="480" height="223" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                      </amp-img>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Step 3</h3>
                        <p>To be able to access the Flash-Video as well, there has to be set a second Port Forwarding. Therefore just follow the manual of this step, with the only difference to to set the Flash-Port instead. So for your first camera all ports are set to 1935, for your second camera it´s 1936, etc.</p>
                        <p>Now all Port Forwarings for your camera are set in the router. You can now continue with the next step, therefore follow this Link:</a>.</p>

                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                      <div class="margin">
                          <h3>Step III : The Camera´s DDNS-Address and the Remote-Access</h3>
                          <br>
                          <a href="/Internet_Access/Mobile_Access/"><button type="button" class="btn">Step III</button></a>
                      </div>
                      <!-- /margin -->
                </article>
